1  Evaluation Summary                                             4028 1451
=====================                                             4028 1451
                                                                  4028 1451
    Zirconium is used in fuel rods cladding due to its            4028 1451
corrosion-resistance and low thermal neutron absorption           4028 1451
cross-section. It is also considered in advanced reactor design   4028 1451
studies as a moderator (in the form of zirconium hydride) and as  4028 1451
inert matrix fuel material. The ENDF/B-VI.8 files evaluated in    4028 1451
the 1970's relied heavily on experimental data and lacked         4028 1451
quantities such as double-differential cross sections and gamma   4028 1451
production.                                                       4028 1451
  For ENDF/B-VII.0, The NNDC (BNL) performed a new evaluation of  4028 1451
the fast neutron region in 91Zr using the EMPIRE code, which      4028 1451
provided acceptable description of the total cross section on     4028 1451
91Zr and contained a higher elastic scattering cross section.     4028 1451
This evaluation was accepted by KAPL and Bettis and adopted by    4028 1451
CSEWG for the final release of ENDF/B-VII.0. Integral testing of  4028 1451
ENDF/B-VII.0 performed after its release revealed that the new    4028 1451
set of Zr evaluations over predict reactivity in the TRIGA C132   4028 1451
and C133 benchmarks by more than 500 pcm. In addition, new not    4028 1451
yet published measurements of the total cross section on natural  4028 1451
Zr performed by RPI indicated that ENDF/B-VI.8 values were much   4028 1451
closer to the new data than those of ENDF/B-VII.0. Finally,       4028 1451
continued testing at KAPL showed that ENDF/B-VI.8 performance     4028 1451
was still superior compared to all modern libraries.              4028 1451
  In the old ENDF/B-VI.8 evaluation and in the experimental       4028 1451
data, there are pronounced fluctuations in the total and elastic  4028 1451
cross sections below 1 MeV indicating either resonance structure  4028 1451
or potentially insufficient level density for statistical model   4028 1451
treatment, most likely related to the closed neutron shell in     4028 1451
90Zr. In the new evaluation we describe below, we attempt to      4028 1451
preserve the completeness of the model based evaluations without  4028 1451
losing the experimental information that cannot be reproduced     4028 1451
within reaction theory. While doing this, we make use of          4028 1451
advanced approaches such as coupled-channel soft-rotor optical    4028 1451
potential and microscopic, parity dependent level densities.      4028 1451
