3.3  Unresolved Resonance Region                                  4028 1451
--------------------------------                                  4028 1451
                                                                  4028 1451
  In the unresolved resonance region, we deduce an average level  4028 1451
spacing and strength functions for s-wave by fitting of reduced   4028 1451
widths of resolved resonances to the Porter-Thomas distribution.  4028 1451
We adopted the strength function for p-wave from [6] and the      4028 1451
average radiative widths for s- and p-wave neutrons of 127 meV    4028 1451
and 223 meV, respectively were obtained from [5, 6, 4]. For       4028 1451
d-wave neutrons, we obtain a capture width of 148.6 meV from the  4028 1451
geometric mean of the s- and p-wave components. We took the       4028 1451
energy-dependence of the level spacing to be the Gilbert-Cameron  4028 1451
level density formula with associated parameters from Mughabghab  4028 1451
[4, 9]. Further, we took the energy-dependence of capture widths  4028 1451
to be the generalized Fermi liquid model [9] with associated      4028 1451
parameters from [4]. We use an effective scattering radius of     4028 1451
7.2 fm in the URR.                                                4028 1451
